The paper discusses vulnerabilities in deep reinforcement learning (DRL) agents, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses security issues, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of policies, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of reward modification, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
